Follow all the steps in the Raspberry Pi Imager
You can download the latest version in https://www.raspberrypi.com/software/

Choose your device:  Raspberry Pi 3/4/5
OS:                  Other specific-purpose OS -> 3D Printing -> Mainsail -> MainsailOS
Choose Storage:      MicroSD
*Customisation*
Hostname:            vzbot330
Localisation:        Your location
Username:            pi 
Password:            choose a secure password, but keep it practical as you will type it often
Choose Wi-Fi:        Secure Network & add here your network details
Network note:        I strongly recommend an Ethernet connection during the printer setup otherwise you will need usb-keyboard to reconnect your wifi
Enable SSH:          Yes with Password authentication 
Write image:         Quick check and write

After flashing, safely eject the SD card before inserting it into the Raspberry Pi.

IMPORTANT:
WiFi can fail or reset during initial setup or updates.
If this happens, you will lose SSH access and cannot reconnect without a keyboard and screen.

Recommendation:
Use Ethernet during the initial setup to ensure stable access.
